@startuml 09B-sequence-cv-evidence-upload
' CVerify — CV / evidence attachment upload and retrieval.
' Verified against:
'   Modules/Profiles/Controllers/EvidenceController.cs
'       [Route "api/v1/users/evidence"]:15, [Authorize]:16,
'       UploadEvidence:39-70 · GetEvidenceDownload:72-80 · DeleteEvidence:82-90
'   Modules/Profiles/Services/AttachmentService.cs
'       UploadAttachmentAsync (module resolution, UploadFileAsync, ProfileAttachment insert,
'       GetSignedUrlAsync 1 h) · GetAttachmentSignedUrlAsync · DeleteAttachmentAsync
'   Modules/Shared/Storage/Services/R2StorageService.cs
'       ValidateFile:82-131 · UploadFileAsync:137-232 (Polly retry :52-79) · GetSignedUrlAsync:278-303
'   Modules/Shared/Storage/Constants/StorageConstants.cs   (size limits, MIME allowlists, extension blocklist)
'   Modules/Shared/Storage/Utilities/StorageKeyGenerator.cs (GenerateKey — ULID key layout)
'   Modules/Shared/Storage/Services/EncryptedFileStorageService.cs (AES-GCM path — recovery claims only)
' Ground truth: GROUND-TRUTH.md §6.1 (no OCR/parsing pipeline), §7 (MinIO in prod behind R2_* env names).

title CVerify — Evidence Upload (POST api/v1/users/evidence/upload)

skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam maxMessageSize 300

actor       "Candidate"                            as U
participant "Next.js Client"                       as C
participant "nginx (host-installed)"               as N
participant "EvidenceController"                   as EC
participant "AttachmentService"                    as AS
participant "R2StorageService\n(IStorageService)"  as R2
participant "StorageKeyGenerator"                  as KG
database    "PostgreSQL"                           as DB
database    "MinIO\n(S3-compatible, prod)"         as S3

== Upload ==
U  -> C  : select file (+ entityType, entityId)
C  -> N  : POST /api/v1/users/evidence/upload  (multipart/form-data, cookies)
N  -> EC : proxied to 127.0.0.1:5247
EC -> EC : reject if file null/empty or entityType blank -> 400
EC -> AS : UploadAttachmentAsync(userId, entityType, entityId,\nstream, fileName, contentType)

AS -> AS : entityType -> StorageModule\n"Avatar" => Profile; otherwise Evidence
AS -> R2 : UploadFileAsync(stream, fileName, contentType, module)

group ValidateFile — the only inspection performed on the file
    R2 -> R2 : stream readable?
    R2 -> R2 : extension not in UnsafeExtensions\n(.exe .bat .cmd .sh .js .vbs .scr .com .msi)
    R2 -> R2 : size <= module limit\n(Profile 2 MB · Certificate 10 MB · Evidence 20 MB\n· Temporary 5 MB · default 5 MB)
    R2 -> R2 : MIME in AllowedImageTypes (jpeg/png/webp/gif)\nor AllowedDocumentTypes (pdf, doc, docx);\nProfile module accepts images only
    note right of R2
      Size is only checked when `fileStream.CanSeek` is true.
      The MIME type is the client-supplied Content-Type — no magic-byte
      sniffing, so the check is advisory rather than authoritative.
    end note
end

R2 -> KG : GenerateKey(fileName, module)
KG --> R2 : {prefix}/{yyyy}/{MM}/{dd}/{ULID}{ext}\nprefix ∈ profiles|achievements|certificates|evidence|temp
R2 -> R2 : copy to seekable MemoryStream (so Polly can retry)
R2 -> R2 : metadata userId (from ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier\nvia IHttpContextAccessor, else "system"), module, uploadedAt
R2 -> S3 : PutObject(bucket = R2.BucketName, key, DisablePayloadSigning = true)\nPolly: 3 attempts, exponential + jitter on 5xx/IO/timeout
S3 --> R2 : ok
R2 --> AS : StorageFileDto { Bucket, ObjectKey, MimeType, Size }

AS -> DB : INSERT ProfileAttachment\n(UserId, EntityType, EntityId, FileName,\nFilePath = ObjectKey, FileSize, FileType)
AS -> R2 : GetSignedUrlAsync(objectKey, 1 h)
R2 -> S3 : GetPreSignedURL(GET, expires +1 h)
AS --> EC : AttachmentResponse { id, fileName, size, type, signedUrl }
EC --> C  : 201 Created (Location -> GET {id}/download)

note over EC, S3 #ffdddd
  **GROUND-TRUTH §6.1 — there is NO OCR / parsing pipeline on upload.**
  The bytes are validated, keyed, encrypted-at-rest by the storage
  backend only, stored, and a row is written. Nothing else happens:
  * no text extraction — the 5 extractors in `CVerify.AI/shared/extractors/`
    are dead code; no module under `app/` imports them (tests only)
  * no embedding — `repository/embedding/__init__.py` is literally
    `# Pruned embedding module`, and no vector library is in requirements.txt
  * no skill extraction, no SFIA/O*NET mapping, no scoring is triggered
  * the AI service is never called on this path
  The uploaded file influences an assessment only if a human later
  references it; `profile_attachments.EntityId` is polymorphic with
  **no FK** (GROUND-TRUTH §4.1 hazard 5).
end note

== Download ==
U  -> C  : open attachment
C  -> EC : GET /api/v1/users/evidence/{id}/download
EC -> AS : GetAttachmentSignedUrlAsync(userId, id)
AS -> DB : ProfileAttachments where Id = id AND UserId = userId
alt not found / not owner
    AS --> EC : ResourceNotFoundException -> 404
end
AS -> R2 : GetSignedUrlAsync(FilePath, 1 h)
EC --> C : 302 Redirect to the presigned URL
note right of EC
  Ownership is enforced by the `UserId == CurrentUserId` predicate in
  the query — there is no organization- or role-scoped sharing path.
  Once issued, the presigned URL is a bearer capability valid for 1 h
  regardless of subsequent permission changes.
end note

== Delete ==
C  -> EC : DELETE /api/v1/users/evidence/{id}
EC -> AS : DeleteAttachmentAsync(userId, id)
AS -> S3 : DeleteObject(FilePath)
note right of AS
  A storage failure here is swallowed — it is caught and written with
  `Console.WriteLine`, then the DB soft-delete proceeds anyway. The
  object can therefore be orphaned in the bucket with no row pointing
  at it and no retry mechanism.
end note
AS -> DB : set DeletedAt (soft delete)
EC --> C : 204 No Content

note as N_Enc
  A second, unrelated storage service exists:
  `EncryptedFileStorageService` performs client-side chunked AES-256-GCM
  (64 KB blocks, per-chunk nonce derived from a 12-byte base nonce plus a
  big-endian counter) and writes to `claims/{claimId}/{sha256}.bin`.
  It is used **only** by the organization-recovery reclaim flow, not by
  evidence upload. Its key is SHA-256 of the configured JWT signing key,
  so rotating the JWT key would make every stored claim document
  undecryptable.
end note
N_Enc .. R2

note as N_Deploy
  Class names, log strings and env keys all say "Cloudflare R2", but
  GROUND-TRUTH §7 confirms production runs **self-hosted MinIO** — the
  `R2_*` names were kept because the AWS S3 SDK client is generic.
end note
N_Deploy .. S3

@enduml
